verses.roman:
eke eke sarva-bhakte kaila sambhāṣaṇa
sabā lañā abhyantare karilā gamana

synonyms: eke eke—one after another; sarva-bhakte—to every devotee; kaila—did; sambhāṣaṇa—address; sabā lañā—taking all of them; abhyantare—inside; karilā gamana—entered.
translation: The Lord addressed all the devotees one after another and took all of them with Him into the house.
